bark: smooth throughout, grey.
rough over part or all of trunks, box-type to fibrous, rarely smooth throughout, grey, yellow-grey and grey-brown, smooth above, grey over green-brown.
rough to small branches, stringy or fibrous, grey to grey-brown.
smooth throughout, powdery, white over pale orange to creamy pink.
smooth, mottled shades of pale grey, pink-grey and brown-grey.
rough to small branches, fibrous, grey or grey-brown, held in flattish strips rather than typical stringybark.
rough on part or all of trunk, box-type or sometimes tessellated, grey or blackish, large branches and sometimes upper trunk smooth-barked, white to grey.
partly rough with loose, papery or brittle ribbons of imperfectly shed pale grey-brown bark on at least base of or over most of trunk, smooth bark whitish to pink, pale orange or grey.

rough, dark grey, fairly firm and scaly or flaky to fibrous for about half of to all of trunk and large limbs to ca 15 cm diameter, becoming slightly tessellated on older trees, smooth above, dull pinkish grey to whitish.
rough to small branches, stringy or fibrous, dark grey or grey-brown.
smooth, new bark pale orange to pale pink to pale yellow to creamy-white, maturing to white and weathering to grey or reddish brown just before decortication.

rough on most or all of trunk and base of large branches, rarely extending to branches 8 cm diameter, box type, often becoming tessellated, pale grey or mottled grey and white patches, smooth bark of branches predominantly white, sometimes grey, or tinged orange, pink or salmon.
rough on part or most of stems, fibrous to box-type, grey to grey-brown, or smooth throughout, grey to pink-grey or coppery brown, the crown sometimes ribbony.
smooth throughout, pale shiny grey over grey-brown to bronze.
rough to small branches or rarely the branches 8cm diameter smooth, rough bark thick, fibrous, coarsely furrowed down trunk, grey; branchlets rarely glaucous.
rough, usually to the base of the branches, sometimes only on the lower trunk, fibrous, grey-brown. Upper trunk and branches with grey to grey-brown over orange to bronze smooth bark.
smooth throughout or with loose, greyish slabs persistent at base of trunk, smooth bark often becoming granular with age, white, grey, cream, brown or orange.

rough on part or all of trunk and to base of large branches, finely fibrous peppermint type, dark grey to grey-brown, smooth bark white to grey, or brownish, sometimes with ribbons of decorticated bark held in the upper branches.
rough throughout or only on trunk and large branches, finely fibrous (like peppermints), grey or grey-brown, smooth bark whitish.
rough on trunk and branches, shortly and closely fibrous, often tessellated, grey, or mottled with grey and white patches, horizontal black scars sometimes present on trunk.
rough for basal ca 1m of stem, grey, smooth above.

smooth throughout with some grey, loose imperfectly decorticated strips of rough bark accumulating on lower stems; smooth bark pale grey, grey-brown, white or pinkish to coppery with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
smooth throughout, mottled pale grey, pale brown, orange and whitish, ribbons sometimes present.
rough hard and dark grey on lower ca 2 m of trunk,smooth greyover cream above that. Young reproductive trees may lack or have virtually no rough bark.
b usually smooth throughout, of 'oily' appearance, grey and red-brown to yellowish green.
smooth throughout, greyish.
smooth, cream, grey, brown or green.
smooth and very powdery throughout, new bark pale pink to pale yellow, maturing to white and sometimes weathering to grey just before decortication. branchlets very glaucous.
rough throughout, grey or grey-brown, fibrous, sometimes prickly to touch, held on trunk in flattish strips rather than typical stringybark.
smooth, grey, yellow, brown or greenish, occasionally with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
rough, grey-black for up to 2-3 m of trunk, tightly fibrous and fissured to flaky, smooth above, grey and yellowish brown.
smooth, grey-green, grey, pinkish, white or brown, sometimes with horizontal black scars.
rough to small branches in trees, stringy, grey or brown; in mallees shortly fibrous to flaky on stems with branches smooth.
rough, extending to limbs to about 5 cm diameter, fibrous, peppermint-type, dark grey, smooth bark cream andpale grey.
smooth throughout, sometimes with thin flakes or strips of decorticating bark persisting on the lower trunk. Smooth bark grey or reddish grey or brown over white to creamy-white to yellow.
smooth throughout, grey to pale coppery.
smooth throughout or rough for up tohalf the trunk, finely fibrous persistent box-type, grey-brown, smooth bark pale grey to brownish and bronze or orange-pink.
smooth throughout, dark satiny pink-brown to pink-grey or dark red shedding in thin sheets to reveal powdery creamy white.

rough to small branches or branches 8 cm diameter smooth; rough bark thick, furrowed longitudinally, dark grey to blackish, densely fibrous, sometimes with horizontal black scars, smooth branches salmon-coloured, sometimes with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
usually rough over most of the stems, flaky or fibrous, usually held in loose slabs, light grey to yellowish-brown, rarely almost smooth-barked.
rough for up to 2 m of trunks, loose, flaky to ribbony, grey to blackish brown, sometimes smooth throughout, silvery grey to pale brown-grey.
rough to small branches stringy, greyover red-brown.
rough on lower trunk only, compacted, hard, blackish or grey, upper trunk and branches smooth grey, green, cream, brown or white, often with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
smooth, pink, brown, grey, cream or green.
rough on trunk and larger branches, stringy or fibrous, grey to reddish-brown.
rough flaky grey-black, red-grey or grey-brownbox-type on trunk often extending to branches 6 cm diameter, upper branchessmooth-barked and grey to pinkish-grey or orange.
rough, firm (compacted), fibrous to flaky on lower half of stems, dark grey, then shedding in short ribbons above to show smooth grey-brown to pink-brown and cream bark.
smooth, sometimes becoming granular with age, mottled white, grey, orange, pink or brown.
rough on trunk and larger branches, fibrous or box-like, flaky, grey or grey-brown, smooth branches yellow.
smooth throughout or with loose, grey slabs of rough bark at base or trunks, smooth bark grey, white, cream, green, yellow or brown, often with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
rough over part or all of trunk, fibrous to flaky, dark grey, then becoming smooth, grey-brown to brown.
rough over trunk and branches, box-type, grey or mottled grey and white patches, branchlets occasionally glaucous. crown of mature tree often consisting of juvenile leaves.
rough and stringy to small branches, grey to brown-grey.
smooth throughout, pink and pink-grey (sometimes with thin curls of semi-persistent bark forming an attractive ring 5 cm high at the base of the trunk).
on lower trunk rough, fibrous to box-type, dark brown to black, upper trunk and branches smooth, grey-brown to yellowish green or coppery, often with ribbons of decorticated bark on the branches.
rough on part or all of trunk and branches to 6 cm diameter, stringy, grey or brown, branches smooth above.
smooth throughout or with partially adherent brownish rough bark at base of trunk, smooth bark bluish grey or white, branches ribbony.
smooth throughout, new bark pale orange to pale creamy-pink, maturing through brilliant salmon-pink to grey-white and weathering to grey just before decortication. Mature bark sometimes powdery.
smooth throughout or with some loose rough grey bark at base of trunk, smooth bark pale grey, cream and white with patches of yellow, pink, brown or orange.
smooth, grey over bronze, yellow-green or coppery, rarely with a very short stocking of brown fibrous rough bark.
rough on trunk and branches 10cm diameter, stringy, dark brown to grey-brown, branches smooth-barked, whitish.
rough throughout, stringy, grey to grey-brown. Branchlets slightly glaucous and strongly quadrangular, forming wings at each edge.

partly or wholly rough on trunk but sometimes almost smooth, branches always smooth; rough bark box-type, thin and flaky, mottled grey and white patches or grey-brown, smooth bark white, cream, yellow or grey, sometimes with with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
rough on trunk and larger limbs in thick, elongated, fibrous, grey or brown strips; smooth bark predominantly white, cream, or pale brown.
b'rough to small branches, fibrous to stringy, grey to brown or sometimes the larger branches smooth, grey to white.

of trees fibrous and fissured yellow-brown to dark grey on part or all of trunk with branches smooth grey, brown, orange or pinkish to white. In mallees stems are smooth except for a short stocking of rough bark; the upper stems and branches may be ribbony.
partly rough over trunk with imperfectly shed strips of greyish bark, smooth above, bronze and dark grey.
smooth throughout,grey to silvery grey and salmon, shedding in irregularstrips.

rough, usually only on the lower trunk for 2-4 m, sometimes rough to the small branches, often compacted and hard and fissured like that of an ironbark, dark grey to black. Smooth bark grey over white to creamy-yellow to orange.
smooth throughout, powdery white, weathering in patches to pink or grey.
firm, fibrous to coarsely flaky, rough over part or all of trunk and often extending to ca 5 cm diameter branches, smooth above grey and bronze to salmon-pink.
rough to ca 3 cm diameter branches, thick, long-fibred, fissured, tending to papery on the outside, grey-brown over red-brown.
rough over whole trunk and larger branches, fibrous, usually tessellated and mottled grey and white.
smooth throughout, shiny, mottled light grey, salmon pink and creamy white.

rough, brown or grey, fibrous on lower 1-6 m of trunk, smooth above, white, cream, pinkish, orange, or olive-green to coppery, sometimes with horizontal black scars, often with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
smooth, new bark pale orange, maturing to mottled grey, becoming granular with age,.
smooth, greenish brown and cream, shedding in ribbons.
smooth throughout, white, pink, orange, pale brown or grey.
rough on basal part of trunk consisting of persistent thin strips of grey-brown bark, smooth above grey and coppery to pink.

rough and compacted, dark grey, grey-brown or black, on 1-6 m of trunk, or with some loose basal slabs, smooth above, mostly green-grey often with a few ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches, branchlets sometimes glaucous.
minnirichi on trunk and branches, reddish-brown.
smooth throughout, grey, cream, white and orange, shedding in ribbons.
smooth, pale greenish grey, shedding in strips.
rough to small branches, stringy, grey to grey-brown.
rough over part of trunks, box-type to tessellated on older stems, grey-brown, smooth above, grey, grey-brown and yellow-cream, shedding in ribbons.

rough over the lower part of the trunk only, for up to 0.7 m, blackish grey, loose, fissured, fibrous, shedding in strips at its upper limit, smooth on upper trunk and branches, white to cream, pink and pale grey;sometimes smooth throughout.
smooth throughout, often powdery, predominantly white, cream or grey but with patches of pink, red or brown.
rough for 2 to 3 m on the lower trunk, usually hard, tessellated or box-type, dark grey to black with abrupt change to smooth bark, which is normally white to grey, rarely creamy pink to yellow.
rough and stringy to the small branches, grey or brown-grey.
rough, coarsely fissured and stringy to small branches, grey or grey-brown.
smooth throughout, shiny, greenish grey to yellow-brown, red-brown or coppery.

smooth throughout or partly rough on lower trunk; rough bark either loose basal slabs, or compacted, dark brown, grey or blackish; smooth bark white-grey to grey-green, green or yellow-grey, sometimes slightly powdery.
smooth, becoming granular with age, predominantly grey or cream with brown, pink or orange patches.
rough, grey and flaky on stems and branches to ca 5 cm diameter, smooth above, light grey over brown.

smooth throughout or with some persistent rough, greyish bark at the base of trunk; smooth bark often powdery, white, cream, pale grey, yellow-orange or pink, sometimes horizontal black scars present, at times with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches; branchlets glaucous.
rough to small branches, stringy, grey or grey-brown.
smooth throughout, whitish grey to grey or mottled with brown.
rough to small branches, stringy or fibrous, grey or grey-brown.
smooth throughout, grey over coppery, pinkish or cream, sometimes a short (ca 0.5 m) stocking of crumbly to flaky rough grey-black bark present.
rough and flaky grey-brown for up to half of trunk then smooth, or smooth over whole stems, mottled whitish and pink-grey to salmon.
rough throughout, thick or the branches smooth; rough bark fibrous, longitudinally fissured, grey or grey-brown over red-brown, smooth bark pale brown to cream, branchlets often glaucous.
pale grey and white mottled, sometimes powdery.
rough for up to 3 m of the trunks of larger plants, with grey-brown shaggy, ribbony bark not shedding cleanly, smooth above, or on smaller plants smooth throughout, creamy grey to grey-brown.
smooth throughout, dark grey to black over greenish yellow, shedding in strips.

on trunk partly or completely rough, fibrous and finely fissured longitudinally grey or brown-grey, branches smooth, light brown to creamy-white or pale grey, with long ribbons of decorticated bark in the branches, branchlets sometimes glaucous.
rough to small branches, thick, fibrous, furrowed longitudinally, grey over red-brown.
smooth, mottled white, yellow, pink, orange, brown, pale grey, dark grey or blue grey, sometimes slightly powdery.
smooth throughout, dark and whitish grey over brownish, or mottled with imperfectly shed flakes of brown-grey rough bark.

rough, grey-brown to orange-brown to yellowish grey, over most of or whole trunk and sometimes extending to larger branches down to 20 cm diameter, smooth above. Rough bark thick,soft and flaky to fibrous becoming coarsely tessellated on older trunks; smooth bark white to grey-brown to orange.
rough, narrowly fissured longitudinally, compacted, grey or brown-grey, upper stems and branches usually smooth, whitish to pale yellow-grey.
smooth throughout or with a few loose basal grey slabs, smooth bark grey, cream, white, pinkish and fawn, occasionally with horizontal black scars, branchlets often glaucous.
rough, grey, shaggy to ribbony on part or all of trunks to 10 cm diameter branches, or on smaller mallees stems smooth throughout, pinkish grey to whitish and yellow-green.
smooth throughout, shedding in short ribbons, pale grey and pinkish grey over coppery to white.
rough grey-brown, thick to flaky or scaly for up to half of trunk, or sometimes entirely smooth, pale grey over coppery.
smooth throughout, greyor light grey, peeling to yellow cream, shedding in strips.
smooth throughout, powdery white over pale pink, weathering in patches to grey.
smooth throughout, shedding in short strips, pale grey over creamy white.
grey-brown stringybark to small limbs, branchlets may be smooth.
rough on trunk and branches to about 8 cm diameter, box-type, often tessellated or flaky, grey or grey-brown, smooth bark whitish.

rough on most of trunk often extending to branches 8 cm diameter, finely fibrous, grey, grey-brown or greyish yellow, sometimes prickly, sometimes with horizontal black scars; smooth bark white or grey.
rough to branches ca 3 cm diameter,loosely fibrous, longitudinally furrowed, grey over red-brown; branchlets glaucous.
usually smooth, grey-brown over green, sometimes larger mallees with a short stocking of grey-brown ribbony rough bark.
rough on part or all of trunk, sometimes extending to the largest limbs, box-type or sometimes tessellated, grey, grey-brown or blackish, upper bark smooth, powdery, white, cream, pale grey or pink.
smooth throughout or with some persistent flaky-fibrous rough grey bark at the base of the stem, smooth bark powdery white over pale grey to pinkish grey.
smooth, mottled, greenish, white, brown, blue-greyand grey; on tallest trees there may be some basal slabs of rough grey-brown bark low on trunk; branchlets glaucous, squared in cross-section.
wholly smooth, pale grey and pale brown.
usually rough dark grey to brown or yellow brown and scaly, flaky or thinly fibrous for up to 2 m of trunk, smooth above grey over salmon pink, sometimes prickly.
rough on trunk, sometimes extending to small branches, fibrous, sometimes fissured and forming longitudinal slabs, sometimes tessellated in part, grey; smooth bark grey, grey-brown to pale orange.
smooth throughout or with a few loose basal grey or brown rough slabs; smooth bark becoming granular with age, white to cream, grey, blue-grey or yellow.
rough on trunk only or extending to 8 cm diameter branches in older trees, compacted, grey, brown or black; smooth bark grey, yellow or grey-brown, branchlets glaucous or non-glaucous.
smooth throughout, shiny, grey over bronze to greenish brown.
rough, grey and coarsely flaky for lower part of stems, smooth above, pale grey to creamy yellow and pale brown; branchlets glaucous.
rough on lower trunk for up to 1 m, with imperfectly shed grey curls, smooth above, grey over pinkish.

rough throughout or branches less than 8 cm diameter smooth; rough bark finely fibrous (peppermint-type), grey or grey-brown; smooth bark white or grey, often with scribbles, branchlets glaucous or non-glaucous.
thick, rough, densely and closely fibrous on most of trunk and larger branches, minnirichi only on smaller branches, green-fawn over rich red-brown.
smooth, grey, often with scribbles.
smooth and powdery throughout, new bark pale pink, maturing to white. Branchlets glaucous.
smooth throughout, grey to silvery, shedding in short curly brown flakes.

smooth or with a ragged stocking of partly shed grey or red-brown strips on lower stems; smooth bark pink to brown, or white to grey or orange-brown, often with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
smooth throughout, whitish grey to cream, brown and pinkish grey.
smooth throughout, white to pale grey and yellowish grey.
smooth throughout or sometimes with rough grey-brown loosely adherent thin flaky bark on base of stems, smooth bark pinkish grey to white, powdery at times.

smooth throughout, yellowish, pale grey, cream or grey-brown or orange-brown, or with some persistent slabs of rough bark or thin rough bark on lower trunk; often with horizontal bark scars on rough or smooth bark, ribbons of decorticated bark sometimes present.

smooth throughout or with short stocking of persistent rough greyish bark; smooth bark yellow or white to cream with patches of grey, pink, brown and green, sometimes powdery, sometimes with horizontal black scars, often with ribbony crown.

smooth to small branches, or with a short stocking of persistent, flaky, grey or grey-brown rough bark; smooth bark often slightly powdery, mottled white, orange, brown, grey or yellow, branchlets glaucous.
smooth throughout, or partly rough due to persistent slabs of grey bark on base of trunk; smooth bark white, grey, yellow, pink, brown, coppery or orange, branchlets glaucous.
smooth throughout, or sometimes with some persistent scaly grey or grey-brown bark at base of trunk; smooth bark white or cream, with patches of yellow, pink, grey or orange, sometimes powdery.
smooth throughout, pale whitish grey over salmon and yellow-green, surface may be powdery.
smooth throughout, dark or pale grey to whitish.

rough on all or part of trunk, usually not furrowed, stringy or fibrous, grey to black, sometimes with horizontal black scars; smooth bark white, cream, yellow, grey or grey-green, often with scribbles, occasionally with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches, branchlets glaucous or non-glaucous.
rough over most or on the lower portion of stem, dark grey to grey-brown, fibrous to scaly, smooth bark above white to pink-grey.

usually rough on lower trunk, rough bark compacted, grey or brown; smooth bark white, cream, pink, green or grey, usually with scribbles, often ribbony. Young reproductively mature trees maylack any rough bark.
smooth throughout, grey over pale coppery and brown.

smooth except for some loose rough grey, black or brown bark at base of trunk; smooth bark white, cream, yellow, brown, green or grey, horizontal black scars usually present on trunk, often ribbons of decorticated bark hang in the upper branches.
pale grey to grey and salmon-brown.
smooth, grey, brown, pink, white or yellow.
smooth throughout, silvery white to greenish grey and coppery, or with a very short basal stocking of rough flaky grey-brown to blackish bark.
smooth throughout, with oily sheen, greenish grey to bronze, coppery or brown.
smooth throughout, creamy brown and pale grey, sometimes with persistent coarse ribbons of greyish rough bark for up to 1 m of stems.
wholly smooth, light grey to grey andbrown over orange to yellow, creamy whiteor light tan; shedding in long ribbons conspicuously hangingfrom branches to ground level in springtime.
rough on lower trunk of shrubs, in mallees extending to ca 4 cm diameter branches, fibrous, greyish brown.
rough to the large branches, finely fibrous (peppermint-type), grey to grey-brown; smooth bark grey.
rough for 2-3 m over the lower trunk, fibrous, flaky; smooth bark grey to white over orange-cream.
smooth throughout, pale grey over pale orange to pale brown, shedding in broad ribbons.
rough, thin and flaky to hard and furrowed, grey to yellowish brown, for ca 0.5 m of trunk, smooth above, pale grey-brown.
smooth throughout, powdery white over reddish or greenish brown, rarely with a short stocking of flaky rough grey-black bark.
smooth throughout, silvery grey and green-grey over pale brown-orange.

smooth throughout or with some grey to grey-brown slabs of rough bark persisting on base of trunk; smooth bark sometimes slightly powdery, white, cream, pink or grey, often with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
smooth throughout, often powdery, whitish to grey and red-brown mottled.

usually rough on lower part of stems, grey or grey-brown, flaky or box-type; smooth bark white, yellow, grey, brown or pink-grey, shedding in ribbons from the upper stems and branches, rarely powdery.
rough, tightly held, blackish, scaly or tessellated for 2-3 m or more of trunk, then smooth blackish grey-green over coppery.

rough for up to 4 m then smooth; rough bark loose basal slabs or corky, grey or brown; smooth bark usually white to cream, with patches of yellow, grey or green, long ribbons often hanging from crown.
smooth throughout, rarely with a few loose basal slabs of rough bark; smooth bark white or cream with grey, orange or brown patches, sometimes powdery.
usually smooth, grey to creamy-brown, sometimes grey over salmon-pink, larger individuals with a short stocking of light grey to brown flaky rough bark.
smooth throughout, silvery grey and cream-grey over pale brown-orange.
minnirichi throughout, reddish brown.
smooth throughout or with some persistent rough bark at the base of stems; smooth bark green to grey-green with coppery or brown patches.
smooth, usually powdery, white with yellow, orange or grey patches, horizontal black scars sometimes present on trunk.
smooth grey-brown.
usually rough on the lower half of the stems, fibrous on larger stems, flaky to ribbony and loosely held on smaller stems, grey; smooth bark grey to brown over white.
rough to small branches, stringy, grey or grey-brown.
usually entirely smooth, fawn to grey and cream or whitish grey, may have imperfectly shed broad ribbons near the base of trunk.Pith oil glands present in or absent from branchlets
smooth, grey or grey-brown to cream or white, rarely developing a short stocking of loose thin brown box-bark on the lower trunk.
smooth throughout, dark satiny pink-brown to dark red, shedding in thin sheets to reveal powdery creamy-white.
rough on the lower 2 m, grey to brown, fibrous, flaky, smooth above, white, sometimes cream to brown to green.
rough to small branches, longitudinally fissured, stringy, grey to grey-brown.
minnirichi throughout, greyish over red-brown or green-brown, or, less commonly, partly rough, matted and fibrous on basal 1 m of largest trunks.
smooth throughout, whitish to pale grey over yellow to coppery, shedding in ribbons.
rough throughout extending to branches ca 5 cm diameter, stringy, brownish grey.
rough, usually to small branches, hard, fissured and fibrous, grey.
smooth, of \'oily\' appearance, dark grey to light brownish grey over yellowish green or bronze.Pith glands present in branchlets
smooth throughout, grey to grey-brown, or with some persistent basal fibrous bark.
smooth throughout, mottled silvery grey and pale pink-grey.
with thin grey rough and fibrous for up to 0.5 m of trunks of larger plants or smooth throughout, grey and pale pinkish brown.
loose and rough near base but otherwise smooth, light grey to pinkish grey or creamy white.

rough on trunk and larger branches, fibrous or stringy, often furrowed, grey or brown; smooth bark of branches white, cream, orange, grey or brown, with ribbons of decorticated bark conspicuous in the crown.
usually smooth, pinkish grey over white, cream or grey, but sometimes partly rough and loose or box-like and grey.
usually smooth throughout, grey over white to salmon pink to coppery.Branchlets
rough over part or all of trunks, firmly held, thin and fibrous to loose and flaky, grey to blackish, smooth above pale grey and pale brown.
wholly smooth, grey, grey-brown, rusty brown and greenish grey, ribbons sometimes present.
wholly smooth, grey over pale brown.
rough for basal 1-3 m of trunk with friable surface but black and much hardened beneath, smooth above, grey to creamy white over orange shedding in long ribbons.

rough on basal 4-5 m of trunk, compacted, grey, grey-brown or black; smooth bark white, cream or pale grey, with scribbles, occasionally with horizontal black scars, often ribbony, branchlets sometimes glaucous.
smooth throughout, grey over fawn to brown and salmon, shedding in long ribbons.
rough and crumbly over most of trunk, box-type, blackish; smooth bark greenish grey, or green to brown, or yellow-grey, shedding in thin narrow ribbons.

rough over part or all of the stems sometimes extending to branches to ca 8 cm diameter, fibrous to flaky, grey-brown, smooth above pale tan and grey-brown, shedding in ribbons, but smaller mallees may be smooth-barked.
rough usually to small branches, thick, fibrous, furrowed longitudinally, dark-grey; branches 8cm diameter sometimes smooth.
usually smooth throughout, white to grey to brown, sometimes cream to pink; occasionally with a short stocking of pale grey to yellowy brown rough flaky bark.
smooth throughout, shedding in short curly flakes, satiny grey over salmon-pink.
smooth throughout, pale grey and coppery-orange, shedding in long ribbons.
smooth throughout, mottled grey, white, pinkish, and shades of brown.

smooth throughout or with some rough, flaky or box-type grey or brown bark on lower 2 m of larger stems, the flakes shed imperfectly giving a curly appearance; smooth bark white, cream, pink or grey. Branchlets usually glaucous.
smooth, grey-brown over cream to creamy brown to yellow, sometimes with a short stocking of grey-brown ribbony rough bark.

rough, fibrous, grey or grey-brown, on lower trunk of trees, shedding in ribbons above; smooth bark of upper trunks, and of mallees, white, orange, brown, green, grey, yellow or pink; horizontal black scars often present on trunk; branchlets usually glaucous.
smooth, white and grey with patches of pink, orange or green; sometimes becoming granular or powdery with age.
rough to small branches, stringy, furrowed down trunk, usually grey.

smooth apart from base which has persistent slabs, shedding in large strips and slabs; smooth bark white, cream, grey, pink, yellowish or pale creamy orange, often with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches; branchlets occasionally glaucous.
smooth throughout, new bark pale pink to pale orange, maturing to white and then grey.
rough for basal 0.5-3 m of stems, matted and fibrous to thick, loose and flaky, yellow-brown weathering grey, smooth above coppery-orange to salmon pink.
rough throughout, finely fibrous, flaky and grey, becoming tessellated on large, old stems.
usually smooth throughout, white to pale grey; sometimes with yellow-brown to red-brown flaky scaly rough bark.
b'grey to brown, smooth throughout.
rough over all of trunk, sometimesextending to small branches, or the large branches smooth; rough bark fibrous or box-type, grey, grey-brown, smooth bark white, cream or grey.
smooth throughout, grey and pale tan to coppery.
usually rough on lower stems (rarely smooth throughout), tessellated box-type, flaky or fibrous, grey or brown; smooth bark white, pink, brown or grey, sometimes powdery.
rough, flaky, greyish on basal 1-4 m of trunk, smooth above, powdery, pale grey or white.
smooth and powdery throughout, new bark pale pink, maturing to white. branchlets usually not glaucous, but occasionally glaucous.
smooth, light grey to white with patches of yellow, pink or pale brown.
smooth throughout, becoming granular with age, predominantly grey to whitish to brown, mottled with cream, yellow or orange, shedding in patches.
rough over whole trunks or only on the base of smaller stems, fibrous, slightly fissured, grey to grey-brown.
rough to small branches, fibrous, fissured, grey-brown.

rough for lower half of trunk, grey to brown, loose and flaky, smooth above light grey over pinkish grey to coppery cream.
smooth, white, grey, yellow or silvery grey, with prominent scribbles.
smooth, new bark pale orange to pale pink, maturing to white and grey, becoming granular with age,.
rough on base of or up to half of stems, pale grey, fibrous or shedding in thick strips, or smooth throughout, white and pale grey to greenish-grey.
rough with loose grey ribbons for about half of trunk, smooth above grey and greeny brown over yellow.
rough over trunk and branches to 2-3 cm diameter then smooth, rough bark finely fibrous and prickly to touch, grey or grey-brown.
smooth and powdery throughout, new bark creamy-yellow, maturing to white. branchlets usually not glaucous, but occasionally slightly glaucous.
smooth throughout but with conspicuous ribbons of shed bark, light grey, dark grey and pale pinkish brown.
rough over part or all of trunk, firmly fibrous at base then semi-persistent ribbons above, scruffy, grey-brown, or smooth throughout, grey-green, and grey-brown.
smooth throughout; newly exposed bark not powdery, pale pink to pale orange or buttery yellow, maturing to white or grey and powdery to touch.
rough to branches ca 2 cm diameter, shortly fibrous and flaky box-type, often fissured, becoming tessellated on some older trunks, grey.
rough on the lower 2-3 m of trunk, dark grey to almost black, hard scaly-fibrous, flaky; smooth bark, white to grey to pale pink to pale orange; sometimes slightly powdery.
rough on trunk and larger branches, box-type, flaky, grey, branches 8 cm diameter usually smooth, grey.
on trunk and branches rough, firm, fibrous, with interlocking fissures, spongy, grey or brown, smaller branches shedding in ribbons.
rough to 5 cm diameter branches, stringy, pale grey to grey-brown.

smooth throughout or with some thin persistent strips at the base of largest stems; smooth bark predominantly green, with orange, brown or grey patches, shedding in ribbons from the stems and branches.
smooth throughout, grey and brown to coppery.
smooth throughout, light grey-brown over orange.

smooth throughout or with persistent rough grey to brown ribbons on base of stems, sometimes extending for 1-2 m; smooth bark salmon pink to grey-brown or pale grey, sometimes with a few ribbons on the upper branches.
rough on half to all of trunk, hard, compacted, furrowed shallowly (almost like ironbark), or rarely fibrous, blackish-grey to grey, smooth above whitish and grey.
smooth throughout, shiny, grey to coppery to olive-green.
smooth throughout on smaller plants, greenish grey to pale grey and pale bronze, some basal fibrous grey-brown bark on largest stems.
smooth, mottled grey, white, pink or orange.
rough on lower trunk, rarely over whole trunk, thick, fibrous, often box-type, grey to red-brown; smooth above, predominantly white with grey or brown patches shedding in flakes; branchlets
rough to small branches, stringy, thick, somewhat brittle, grey over red-brown.
rough, coarse, hard, black, furrowed, i.e. typical ironbark, extending to branches ca 3 cm diameter.
rough, flaky to fibrous, grey-brown to yellow-brown, for up to 0.5 m of stems, or smooth throughout, greyish brown.
smooth throughout or with some persistent, fibrous, grey bark on base of trunk; smooth bark yellow to orange-brown or greenish.
smooth, grey or grey-brown to creamy-brown, occasionally with grey, crumbly, fibrous, flaky, ribbony bark persisting on the lower trunk. branchlets
rough to branches ca 3 cm diameter, coarsely fissured and stringy-fibrous, grey.
normally smooth throughout, white to light grey to pink; sometimes with short stocking of grey fibrous rough bark on the larger plants.

rough on part or most of trunk, fibrous or box-type, grey or grey-brown; smooth bark white, cream, brown, grey or green, occasionally with with horizontal black scars, commonly with long ribbons of decorticated bark in the crown; branchlets often glaucous.
smooth throughout, white to grey to brown or pink.
rough, very hard and grey-brown to blackish over lower part of trunk, or smooth throughout on smaller mallees, smooth bark grey-brown and pale brown to pink-orange.
rough, grey and shaggy or flaky on part or all of trunk, sometimes smooth throughout with red-brown and whitish grey to grey-brown bark.

smooth throughout or with some persistent basal slabs of rough brown bark; smooth bark pale coppery to yellow-green or pink-brown or creamy white, at times with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
usually rough over most of the stems and normally extending to the larger branches, flaky fibrous, sometimes fissured, usually firmly held, light grey, smooth bark above grey over red-brown.
rough, black or grey-black, coarsely flaky and fissured to hard and compact for about half of trunk, branches smooth, grey cream and orange.
rough, thin, firmly held on base of trunks, fibrous, dark grey, smooth above bronze to coppery and dark grey, shedding in ribbons along the branches, rarely smooth throughout.
smooth, white to cream, coppery, brown, green-grey or yellow-green, or pink-grey, often with scribbles, often with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
smooth mainly white with patches of cream, grey or orange; branchlets glaucous.
smooth white becoming yellow in spring, powdery.
rough over part or all of trunk, thin, shaggy and scaly or flat with shallow fissures, blackish and orange-brown, smooth above, grey to pale grey and orange to salmon-pink.
rough on trunk and larger limbs, stringy, thick, grey, or grey-brown; branches smooth, whitish-grey.
smooth throughout but often appearing scaly with partly shed plates or flakes of red-brown bark over white to pinkish yellow or pale orange.
smooth throughout or with a few persistent strips at base of stems; smooth bark shedding in ribbons, grey, pinkish grey and yellow to brown.
rough and grey, flaky or fibrous for up to 2 m of stems, or smooth throughout and coppery to grey or greenish grey or creamy brown, shedding in short strips.
rough on trunk and often larger branches, box-type often tessellated, grey; smooth bark white or grey.
rough to small branches, box-type often tessellated, dark grey.
smooth throughout, white to grey and coppery.
usually rough over half of trunk, held in flattish strips or somewhat corky, grey-brown, while on smaller plants bark may be smooth, grey.
rough to small branches, soft and finely fibrous to stringy, grey or grey-brown.
rough, fibrous, loose, grey-brown, for ca 1 m of trunks, becoming curly and flaky then smooth whitish grey to pale orange or pinkish grey.
smooth, grey, white, light pinkish grey or salmon, sometimes becoming granular with age, shedding in long strips.
smooth throughout, mottled red-brown to salmon pink and white, sometimes powdery, rarely rough and flaky to fibrous, grey, on base of larger trunks.
rough, black and crumbly to coarsely flaky on lower trunk, smooth above, coppery orange to creamy grey.
smooth and powdery throughout, new bark pale pink to pale orange, maturing to white and then weathering in patches to dark pink or grey. branchlets sometimes glaucous.

smooth throughout, or with some incompletely shed rough, fibrous to flaky, grey to yellowish brown bark on lower stems; smooth bark yellowish with blue-grey and cream patches; horizontal bark scars sometimes present; branchlets not glaucous.
smooth, pale whitish grey to greenish grey over pink-brown. branchlets
rough to ca 2-3 cm branches, stringy, grey or grey-brown.
rough but thin and more or less looseon part or all of trunk, fibrous, grey-brown; branches smooth pale grey to creamy.
rough, hard, grey, fissured, over most or all of trunks, smooth grey above.
smooth throughout, pale grey, dark grey and orange.
usually rough to the base of the branches, sometimes rough only on the lower trunk, fibrous to flaky, dark grey. Smooth bark grey to pink-brown to orange-brown.

usually rough over most of the stem, occasionally rough on the lower stem only, hard fibrous, fissured grey to grey-brown, larger branches usually smooth-barked, white to grey, rarely pink-grey to green-grey.
rough, fibrous, thin, box-type, irregularly cracked to tessellated or flaky, grey, persisting to smaller branches or branches 8 cm diameter smooth.
smooth throughout, becoming granular with age and predominantly dull grey to grey-brown, shedding irregularly in strips to expose cream to pale orange to coppery new bark.
usually rough over most of the lower stem, hard, fibrous, flaky, grey to brown; occasionally completely smooth-barked, smooth bark grey over coppery-brown, rarely white and slightly powdery.
rough over most or all of trunk, tight, thin and fibrous or of thick loose flakes, grey to blackish or dark brown, branches smooth throughout, shiny, grey and olive green to brown, salmon or bronze.
smooth throughout or rough only at base of trunk, flaky or ribbony and persistent, grey-brown, smooth bark dark to pale grey and pinkish brown to white.
wholly smooth or with a very short basal stocking of pale grey box-type bark. Smooth bark pale grey-white fading to pale brown, shedding in short strips.
smooth throughout, grey to white to pink.
smooth, shedding in strips, white to yellowish or brown, grey or olive.
rough, fissured longitudinally, fibrous, often hard, grey, continuing to smaller branches or the branches 8 cm diameter smooth, ribbons sometimes conspicuous in the crown.
rough to small branches, stringy, grey to red-brown.
usually smooth throughout, grey over grey-brown. pinkor salmon, rarely with a basal stocking of rough blackish bark.
smooth throughout, shiny yellowish brown and grey-brown, shedding in short ribbons.
rough to small branches, stringy, often deeply furrowed, grey or grey-brown or red-brown.
rough on trunk and larger branches, shortly fibrous or box-type, thin and flaky, grey and grey-brown smooth bark coppery, brown, grey-green, or grey. branchlets are rarely glaucous.
smooth, becoming granular with age, mottled grey, cream, pink, orange, shedding in strips.
rough on trunk and branches to ca 5-8 cm diameter, tessellated or box-type, thick, grey.
usually rough for up to 4 m of trunk, sometimes extending to ca 8 cm diameter branches, grey-brown, flaky and fibrous, smooth above, grey to white or pale orange.
smooth throughout or with some persistent rough, grey slabs at base of trunk; smooth bark usually powdery, white and grey; branchlets sometimes glaucous.
rough to 5-10 cm diameter branches, stringy in broad flat strips, grey to brown over rich red-brown.
rough to small branches, stringy, deeply fissured, grey or grey-brown.
smooth throughout, pale grey and whitish.
rough, loose, flaky, grey over yellowish on basal part of trunk, otherwise smooth, dark and light grey over pale orange to bronze.
rough throughout, grey or grey-brown to yellowish grey or orange-brown-grey, fibrous, sometimes prickly to touch, held on trunk in flattish strips rather than like typical stringybark.
smooth, cream to cream-brown and bronze-grey.
smooth throughout, mottled dark grey, light greeny grey and orange.
rough to the small branches, grey over grey-brown, finely stringy or fibrous, sometimes quite hard, forming longitudinal furrows.
rough, flaky and grey over all or part of trunk, smooth above grey to pale grey over salmon pink.
fibrous or thin flakes held in variable amounts on trunk, sometime entire trunk rough, yellow-brown to yellow-grey; smooth bark pale grey to yellow; branchlets usually non-glaucous.
rough and flaky, light grey-brown or grey-yellow, for part or all of trunks and base of larger branches, smooth above light grey.
smooth, mottled grey to blue-grey and white, cream, yellow, or pink.
smooth throughout, shedding in ribbons, light grey to pinkish grey and yellow-grey.

rough over whole trunk and to base of larger branches, box-type or tessellated, grey, grey- brown or mottled with grey and whitish patches; smooth bark usually white; pith of branchlets sometimes glandular.
rough to small branches, softly stringy or fibrous, brown-grey to red-brown.
rough throughout, box-type, finely fissured, grey.
smooth throughout, dark and silvery grey over pink.
rough, whitish grey to dark grey, box-type, often deeply fissured, coarsely flaky or becoming tessellated, the branches commonly rough-barked though this feature is variable.
smooth throughout, shiny pale grey-green over coppery brown.

usually wholly smooth, grey, grey-brown, rusty brown and greenish grey, ribbons sometimes present, rarely with a persistent fibrous thin grey-brown basal stocking for ca 0.5 m of trunks on older plants.
smooth white to yellow and creamy-grey; crown ribbony at times.
rough over most of the trunk, hard fibrous, sometimes extending to the larger branches, dark grey to black; smooth bark on upper trunk and larger branches, white to grey to creamy brown to pale pink.
rough on part or all of trunk, thin, box-type or tessellated, grey or mottled with grey and white patches; smooth bark white, cream or pale-grey, often shiny; pith of branchlets sometimes glandular.
smooth and powdery throughout, new bark pale pink, maturing to white or grey. branchlets glaucous.
smooth, grey-brown to pale coppery with patches of orange and yellow.
loose grey-black basal slabs for 1-2 m of trunk then smooth, pale grey, yellowish and pale coppery above; branchlets glaucous.

of trees often rough to smaller branches, in mallees often only at base of stems; rough bark usually compacted, or fibrous or box-type, dark grey; smooth bark grey to green-grey, sometimes with a few ribbons in crown.
rough to small branches, stringy, grey-brown to grey-yellow.
smooth throughout or with 0.5 m of persistent rough bark at the base of stems; smooth bark grey or white; branchlets not glaucous.
rough and coarsely flaky, grey-brown to grey-black usually for only about half of trunks then smooth above, bronze-grey and coppery.
smooth throughout or with persistent rough, fibrous bark on base of trunk for ca 1 m; smooth bark mottled white, grey, brown, cream or orange.
smooth, seasonally powdery, creamy white to yellowish and greeny bronze, shedding in short ribbons.

rough, fibrous, fissured longitudinally and grey to brown on trunk of larger plants, otherwise smooth, grey-green to yellow-brown, crown at times ribbony; branchlets glaucous or non-glaucous; new growth tips quite glaucous.
smooth throughout, grey over cream to brown to salmon-pink to coppery (rarely yellow).
smooth throughout, mottled yellow-brown and grey to creamy yellow, shedding in flakes.
rough to small branches, thick, fibrous, grey or grey-brown, longitudinally furrowed.
rough on base of trunk, rarely more, black and flaky, smooth above red-brown over grey to cream or orange.

smooth throughout or with a thin stocking of rough grey bark for basal 1 m of trunk; smooth bark predominantly pale grey to greenish-grey but with patches of white, cream or pale brown with horizontal black scars sometimes present; crown often ribbony.

rough on trunk and limbs of larger trees, and on base of stems in small trees and mallees, loosely woven peppermint-type, grey, trunks of small trees or mallees sometimes entirely smooth-barked; smooth bark cream to grey-green, yellow-grey or pink-brown, scribbles present; crowns often with long ribbons of bark incompletely shed from branches.
smooth, shedding in long ribbons, white and pale grey; sometimes with persistent slabs of rough grey bark at base of trunk.
rough and flaky, grey-brown, box-type, extending over part or all of stems, smooth above dark brown to grey-brown.
rough to small branches, coarse and thick, fibrous or box-type, mottled grey and whitish or grey-brown; sometimes branches 8 cm diameter smooth; branchlets glaucous.
rough to small branches, fibrous, brown-grey, fissured longitudinally forming broad flat strips.
smooth throughout, pale grey to grey-brown over pink-orange.
rough throughout or branches 8 cm diameter smooth; rough bark thick, fibrous, longitudinally furrowed, grey and red-brown.
smooth throughout, mottled grey to pinkish or silvery.
smooth throughout, shiny, grey over pink-orange and coppery.
b'.rough to small branches, box-type or sometimes tessellated, light grey-brown to grey-white.
smooth throughout shedding in ribbons, grey over whitish to pale brown or pink.
rough to small branches or sometimes branches 8 cm diameter smooth; rough bark stringy or fibrous, brown to grey-brown, longitudinally furrowed; smooth bark green or grey.
rough, imperfectly shed grey to brown, ribbony for up to half of the stems thensmooth above, or smooth-barked throughout, grey over yellowish or salmon pink to creamy brown.

rough over part or all of trunk, sometimes extending to large limbs, black to dark grey, fibrous, fissured and often hard, shedding in broad scruffy strips at its upper limit, smooth above, white to pale grey or pale grey-brown, sometimes powdery.
rough and tessellated, scaly, or box-type on lower trunk, dark grey to black with abrupt change to smooth bark, which is grey to coppery, pink, white, yellow or brown.

usually smooth throughout, grey to brown to coppery, sometimes white to cream to pink, occasionally with a short stocking of pale grey to yellowy-brown rough flaky bark. Branchlets normally non-glaucous, rarely glaucous, with no oil glands in the pith.

rough on trunk and on branches to 5-10 cm diameter, tightly held box-type on larger stems, dark grey or grey-brown, smooth bark on branches grey, coppery or brown; branchlets with or without pith oil glands.
rough with semi-persistent broad grey-brown to black ribbons loosely sheathing part or all of trunk extending sometimes to limbs ca 5 cm diameter, or stems smooth throughout, grey and brown mottled.

usually rough on lower stems, flaky or fibrous, usually loose, grey to grey-brown, at times with short ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches; occasionally smooth barked to ground level, cream, grey-yellow, pink, brown or coppery.
rough, thick, flaky and fibrous to branches 5-8 cm diameter, orange-brown or grey.
smooth throughout, grey to whitish over brown-grey, shedding in short strips.
rough only on lower trunk, fibrous or flaky, grey or grey-brown; smooth bark white, cream or grey, often with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
smooth throughout, creamy brown,grey and pale silver grey.
smooth throughout, white to grey to pale pink to pale orange to pale salmon.
rough only on lower trunk, flaky, grey, or smooth throughout grey-green over yellowish, shedding in strips.
of large stems sometimes rough, grey, thick and flaky at the base, otherwise minnirichi on trunk and branches, reddish brown.
smooth throughout, powdery white, weathering in patches to purple.
rough for up to 4 m at base of trunk, loose and grey; smooth bark powdery, cream, white, grey or yellow-brown, usually with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches. Branchlets
rough on the lower trunk, box-type, grey with abrupt change to smooth bark, which is normally white to grey, rarely creamy brown, sometimes shiny.
smooth throughout, mottled silvery grey and pale pink-grey.
smooth throughout, shedding in short strips, coppery and grey-green to silvery grey.
smooth throughout or with loose, rough, grey to grey-brown bark to variable height on trunk; smooth bark white, cream, pale grey or pink-brown, occasionally powdery.
smooth throughout, mottled white, cream, pale grey with newly exposed bark yellow to creamy pink to bright orange; often powdery.
smooth, grey to grey-brown and greenish.
smooth pale brown, shedding in strips to reveal silvery to pale grey-white new bark.
smooth throughout, grey to green or white with newly exposed bark yellow.
smooth throughout or with some persistent, loose fibrous dark brown bark on lower stem; smooth bark pale brown, cream pink or grey, sometimes becoming granular with age.
smooth and powdery throughout, new bark pale pink to pale orange, maturing to white. branchlets very glaucous and 4-angled.
smooth becoming granular with age, mottled grey, brown, yellow or pink.
smooth throughout or with some persistent rough, grey bark on lower trunk; smooth bark predominantly dark grey, at times with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
rough to small branches, stringy, crumbly, corky, fissured deeply longitudinally, grey-brown.
smooth, predominantly white, cream and grey, with yellow patches, usually with scribbles; branchlets glaucous or non-glaucous.
rough throughout, fibrous, flaky grey or reddish-brown, sometimes tessellated or platy and held in long strips or slabs.
smooth, grey and pinkish.
smooth throughout, grey or grey-brown over creamy-brown to pale coppery to pale orange, decorticating in ribbons which occasionally hang in the upper branches.
smooth, white, grey or coppery.
smooth throughout, or rough only at base of trunks of largest individuals; smooth bark light coppery to greenish or white, shedding in ribbons; branchlets usually glaucous with leaf ring scars.
rough to small branches, box-type, grey.
partly or wholly rough on trunk, sometimes extending to base of larger limbs, grey-brown to yellow-brown persistent flakes, smooth above pale grey, dark grey and yellowish cream.
rough, thin, ribbony to flaky to fibrous and fissured over 1-2 m of trunk, bark on upper trunk and branches smooth, pink-grey, whitish grey and dark grey (rarely smooth bark throughout).
smooth throughout or on larger plants rough only at the base with some persistent ribbons, smooth bark pale grey and pale brown.
smooth throughout, grey to brown and orange-pink.
usually smooth, cream to grey and coppery, at times with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
smooth throughout, white and pale grey to pink or coppery.
wholly smooth, light grey to grey brown or greenish grey over orange to yellow; shedding in long ribbons conspicuous in springtime.
rough on lower half of trunk, finely fibrous, grey or grey-brown; smooth bark not powdery or granular, smooth bark cream to white or grey, often with scribbles.
smooth throughout, sometimes powdery, mottled salmon, pink, white, pale grey and brown.
rough on trunk and larger limbs, sometimes also on smaller branches, finely fibrous or peppermint-type, grey or grey-brown; branches usually smooth, white to cream or grey, often powdery.
rough to small branches or the branches 8 cm diameter smooth; rough bark stringy and shallowly fissured down trunk, usually red-brown, often prickly.
smooth and sometimes powdery, new bark pale pink to creamy-white to greenish-white, maturing to white and weathering to grey or reddish brown just before decortication.
smooth throughout, grey-green over coppery brown.
smooth throughout, grey to grey-brown.
rough on trunk and branches, box-type, grey, brown-grey or mottled with grey and white patches; branchlets glaucous or non-glaucous.

rough, box-type and pale grey to grey-brown on lower 1-2 m of stems; smooth light grey to dark grey, brown or pinkish, at times with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches; smaller regenerating plants that are at flowering stage may be entirely smooth-barked; branchlets usually glaucous or rarelynon-glaucous.
rough to small branches, box-type or tessellated, grey to grey-brown.

rough on the short trunk and larger branches of trees, and on lower stems of mallees, box-type, dark grey to dark brown-grey or whitish grey; smooth bark whitish or grey; branchlets with or without oil glands in the pith.
smooth, becoming granular with age, mottled grey, orange, brown and pink; branchlets glaucous or non-glaucous.
smooth, pale grey and brown.
sometimes fibrous at the base to 0.5 m, more usuallywholly smooth and grey to pinkish-grey to greenish-brown.
rough to small branches, stringy, greyand grey-brown.
smooth, becoming granular with age, mottled grey, cream, pink, orange, coppery or yellow, shedding in strips.
smooth, of \'oily\' appearance, dark grey to light brownish grey over yellowish green or bronze.Pith glands present in branchlets
rough, grey, box-type, extending to the small branches.
smooth throughout, grey over pale orange or coppery.
rough for lower half of trunk, fibrous or persistent ribbons, dark grey to grey-brown or blackish, or completely smooth on smaller mallees.
rough, grey, box-type extending to the small branches, flaky or firm and fissured, sometimes with wavy pattern, sometimes becoming tessellated on older trunks.
rough, stringy or fibrous, loose, prickly, not furrowed, grey or grey-brown.
smooth throughout, pale and mid-grey to mottled brown and pinkish white, shedding in long ribbons.
smooth throughout on smaller trees but on larger trees rough, fibrous, grey to grey-brown for ca 1-2 m of trunk; smooth bark white, cream, yellow, pink and grey, decorticating in ribbons.
smooth throughout or with some short thin persistent ribbons at base of old trunks; smooth bark green to grey with brown, coppery or yellow patches; branchlets glaucous.
smooth, grey to pink, yellow-green, brown, cream or white, shedding from stems in ribbons.
smooth throughout, becoming granular with age, predominantly grey with pink, brown, cream, yellow and orange, shedding in patches.
smooth throughout, mottled silvery grey to light grey over cream bark, shedding in strips.
smooth throughout or with a short stocking of persistent ribbony grey-brown bark, smooth bark grey-brown shedding to light brown or reddish grey.
rough to larger limbs, fibrous, grey or brown; smooth bark grey to white, crown sometimes ribbony; branchlets glaucous and square in cross-section.
rough to small branches, box-type, grey or whitish.
of mallees smooth throughout, grey to pale grey over green-pink; trees have a stocking of scaly or flaky rough grey bark for up to 3 m of trunk.
smooth throughout, mottled pale grey, pale brown, pinkish-grey and whitish, ribbons sometimes present on lower trunks.
smooth, rarely powdery, silvery white, cream, pale grey, orange-yellow, with scribbles.
rough on trunk and large limbs, smaller branches smooth; rough bark finely fibrous, peppermint-type, grey; smooth bark pale grey to grey-green.

rough on most or all of trunk and often on bases of large branches sometimes extending to branches 5 cm diameter, box-type, dark grey, thick, becoming fissured and tessellated. Smooth-barked above this, patchy pale grey to pink-grey to grey to green and creamy white shedding in long flakes.
smooth throughout, shiny, greyish green over coppery to red-brown.
smooth throughout, mottled silvery grey and pale salmon-pink.
smooth, grey, green, brown, white, cream and orange, at times with ribbons of decorticated bark in the branches.
smooth, grey and pale brown shedding in short ribbons.

rough for basalpart of trunk, fibrous or with crumbly surface, grey, brown or black, upper trunk smooth-barked; smooth bark cream, grey-green, pale grey, brown or yellow-white, seasonally with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
rough to small branchlets, thick, deeply fissured, dark grey.
rough on whole trunk of trees or base of larger stems in mallees, fibrous, grey to grey-brown, sometimes smooth throughout; smooth bark yellow to grey.
rough to small branches, stringy or fibrous, grey or grey-brown to red-brown, held in long, flat strips with shallow fissures in between.
rough on trunk and larger limbs, box-type, grey, smooth bark grey to green, pink or coppery.
smooth throughout, grey to creamy-grey to orange-brown, shedding in strips and short ribbons.
wholly smooth, grey over whitish grey to pinkish brown, shedding in strips.
smooth throughout, white, pale grey and pale brown to salmon-brown, rarely powdery, or with persistent ribbony rough fibrous grey-brown bark on lower trunk.
smooth throughout, mottled light grey, yellow, white or cream; branchlets glaucous; bark on small limbs show encircling scars left by fallen connate leaves.
rough to small branches, thick, fibrous, spongy, reddish-brown to grey-brown.
rough on trunk and larger branches, fibrous to box-type, the outer layer crumbly, inner layer hard, grey and grey-brown.
smooth throughout, dark and light grey over pinkish grey or yellow-grey and white.
smooth throughoutwhitish, pale grey to pale orange and tan.
rough on the lower trunk, grey to grey-brown, fibrous, flaky; smooth bark above grey to grey-green to creamy green to brownish cream.

smooth throughout or with some patches of persistent rough, greyish bark at the base; smooth bark often powdery, white, cream, pale grey or pink, with horizontal black scars, usually with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches; branchlets glaucous or non-glaucous.
rough to 2 cm diameter branches, softly fibrous, thick, reddish-brown.
rough to small branches, box-type, often tessellated, grey to pale grey.

rough, fibrous, grey over part or all of trunks, becoming tessellated on older trunks, extending sometimes to branches to ca 10 cm diameter, rarely trunks entirely smooth, greyish white and dark grey.
smooth throughout, cream to pale grey, pinkish grey or yellow-green, sometimes with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
smooth throughout, grey and silvery grey, shedding in strips.
rough to small branches, box-type, usually tessellated, grey to black.
smooth throughout, satiny except where recently shed then powdery, new bark pale orange, ageing to white and weathering to grey in patches.
smooth throughout, powdery, white to pale grey over salmon pink.
rough and flaky, grey to grey-brown on basal 1-4 m of trunk, smooth above, bluish grey to cream, green, pink or brown.
smooth throughout, pale grey over salmon-pink to cream, shedding in flakes.
smooth throughout, shiny, steely grey or olive green to tan, coppery or yellow.
rough over part or all of trunk, grey to black and coarsely flaky and crumbly, rarely smooth throughout; smooth bark greenish-grey over pinky brown.
smooth, slightly powdery, pale grey to creamy white and pale coppery, pink or greenish, shedding in ribbons.
rough throughout, fibrous, grey or brown, held in long strips or slabs with shallow furrows.
smooth, powdery, white and grey, shedding in strips.
smooth, sometimes becoming granular with age, mottled grey, white, pink or orange.
usually smooth, white to grey to grey-green to occasionally yellow, sometimes with a very short stocking of grey-brown tessellated, fibrous rough bark.
smooth throughout, pale grey to dark grey.
rough for part or whole trunk and extending to limbs ca 6-10 cm diameter, grey to black, box-type, flaking in short strips, grey to brown, pink or coppery.
smooth, grey over pinkish grey.
rough at least on trunk and often on limbs, firmly fibrous or quite hard, shallowly, longitudinally fissured, grey to grey-brown; smooth bark of branches brown or pale grey.
smooth throughout, white-grey over coppery, shedding in conspicuous long ribbons.Older branchlets

rough on trunk and base of large branches, at first thin, flaky and orange-brown, becoming compact, thick, longitudinally furrowed and dark grey to black as trees age; smooth bark sometimes powdery, white to cream or yellow; branchlets sometimes glaucous.
smooth throughout or with persistent rough grey to brown ribbons on base of trunk extending for ca 1 m; smooth bark grey-brown or pale grey, sometimes with a few ribbons on the upper branches.
of trees rough, compact and black on trunk, smooth above, sometimes powdery, white, cream, or green-brown, very ribbony; mallees usually smooth throughout.
usually persistent on lower trunks, grey to brown, loose flaky, shaggy, ribbony; smooth bark on upper trunks and branches grey over cream, rarely yellowy-green.
rough to ca 5 cm diameter branches, hard and corky, not fibrous, forming multi-layered plates and strips, grey and brown.
smooth, satin-like throughout, silvery grey over coppery, pink and bronze.
rough over trunk and branches, moderately long-fibrous and becoming somewhat compact and shallowly fissured, grey or grey-brown to yellow-brown.
rough to 4 cm diameter branches, firm to corky fibrous, hardly furrowed, grey or black.
smooth throughout, silvery white to pinkish brown, grey-brown and pale coppery, shedding in ribbons.
smooth throughout, grey, orange-grey and whitish, shedding in long ribbons.
rough throughout, tessellated, grey and red-brown.
rough over whole of trunk and branches to ca 4 cm diameter, fibrous, held in long flattened strips, grey-brown over reddish brown.
rough on lower trunk, compact and dark grey to black; smooth bark greenish, at times with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.
rough on lower trunk, compacted, shallowly fissured, grey; smooth bark yellow or creamy white; branchlets glaucous.
wholly smooth grey over brown to cream, shedding in strips.
smooth throughout, grey over bronze to silvery pink.
rough, thick, dark greyish and fibrous over part or all of trunk and sometimes extending to branches ca 5 cm diameter, smooth above creamy brown to pinkish.
rough for basal part of trunk, crumbly to flaky, grey-black and red-brown.
smooth, mottled pale grey, brown, white and pink, often with scribbles, at times with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches.

smooth throughout or with some slabs of fibrous grey to brown bark persistent at base of trunk; smooth bark mottled cream, yellow, pale brown, pinkish and green, often with ribbons of decorticated bark in the upper branches, branchlets non-glaucous.
smooth, mottled light grey, grey-brown, pink and green, branchlets often glaucous.
smooth throughout, pale and dark grey and grey brown to pinkish and coppery.
smooth, pale grey or brown to yellow-green, horizontal black scars often present.
smooth throughout, pale shiny grey over grey-brown to brown.
rough over basal 0.5 m (or less) of trunks, greyish and fibrous, smooth pale grey to creamy brown above, shedding in strips.
smooth throughout, pale grey to silvery grey.
smooth throughout, pale grey to pale pinkish, yellow-green or pale brown, shedding in ribbons.
rough to small branches, stringy, furrowed, grey to grey-brown.
smooth throughout, pale brown-grey, tan and satiny pale grey.
rough to small branches, fibrous, brown-grey, thick even on sapling growth, becoming fissured on larger stems.
smooth throughout or with a few partly decorticated basal slabs of rough bark; smooth bark white to light grey or yellowish; branchlets glaucous.
smooth throughout, rarely powdery, pale grey to whitish over orange to pale brown, shedding in long ribbons.
smooth throughout, rich coppery red and silvery brown to pale grey.
satiny or glossy, dark grey to orange, green-brown or yellowy green.
smooth throughout, mottled white, cream, yellow, pink and grey; sometimes with persistent dark grey flakes of rough bark on base of large trunks.

rough, thin, fibrous, grey over brown to orange, normally only on the trunk and larger branches, sometimes on the lower trunk only. Smooth bark on upper trunk or branches grey to brown to white over greenish-grey to yellowish-grey to yellowish-brown to orange-yellow.
smooth throughout, rarely with semi-persistent broad ribbons for ca 0.3 m of trunk, mottled dark and pale grey to silvery grey.
rough to the small branches, grey over reddish brown, finely stringy or fibrous, forming longitudinal furrows.
smooth throughout andpale grey over pink-copper and white, rarely partly rough with imperfectly shed basal ribbons of brown or grey bark.

smooth throughout or less commonly with a short stocking of tessellated blackish rough bark. Smooth bark pinkish to creamy white with greyish patches. Small curls or flakes of imperfectly shed bark may be present at times on the otherwise smooth stems.
rough on trunk and branches to about 6 cm diameter, stringy with shallow longitudinal fissures, grey and grey-brown.
smooth throughout, new bark pale orange to pale creamy-pink, maturing through brilliant salmon-pink to dull grey-white and weathering to grey just before decortication.
rough, to smallest branches, fibrous, soft yellow-brown, prickly, or the lower trunk only rough and scaly with upper trunk and branches smooth grey to yellow and pinkish brown.
rough, hard, dark grey to blackish, shortly fissured to almost tessellated, over most or all of trunk, branches smooth, various shades of dark grey to black.
smooth throughout, white to grey with pale pink or pale orange patches.

smooth throughout or, for the largest trees, with some compact, dark grey, rough bark at the base of the trunk; smooth bark white to cream or yellow-grey, with scribbles, the stems and crowns ribbony.

partly or wholly rough on trunks with grey to reddish brown curly strips of partly decorticated bark (rarely smooth throughout); smooth bark pale grey to grey-brown, shiny pink-brown to greenish when newly exposed.
smooth over most of the stems or occasionally some stems with fibrous rough bark for basal part to 0.5 m. Smooth bark grey to pink-grey to white over cream to coppery.
rough to small branches, stringy or fibrous, grey or grey-brown.
smooth and powdery throughout, new bark pale yellow to pale pink to pale orange, ageing to white.
smooth throughout, grey to white to orange-brown or coppery, often highly glossy with a silvery appearance.
smooth throughout or rarely with some rough strips retained at base of larger trunks; smooth bark mottled light grey, white, yellow, brown, pink and green; branchlets glaucous.
smooth throughout, white or cream to pale grey and pinkish.
smooth throughout, grey over greenish brown and pink to pale coppery.
smooth throughout, shedding in short ribbons, green-bronze to yellowish green over pinkish grey to brown.
smooth grey or grey-brown.
smooth throughout or, on larger plants, rough, hard, fibrous, finely fissured and greyish brown on base of trunk; smooth bark bronze-brown to greyish white.
smooth throughout, shiny, grey over rich red-brown.
usually smooth throughout, often powdery, mottled grey, brown, coppery, pink, orange and white.

rough for only part of the trunk, rarely for most of the trunk, with the upper trunk and branches smooth. Rough bark long-fibrous and stringy where best developed lower on trunk, diminishing to fibrous/flaky then smooth pale grey and creamy white..

smooth over whole trunk or with a thick stocking of rough bark consistently to 2-6 m above base, fibrous, grey, brown or black; smooth bark often powdery, white to cream, yellow, light grey or pale brown, usually with conspicuous long ribbons of decorticated bark on upper trunk and in crown.
smooth throughout pale grey over powdery white to pinkish; sometimes with scribbles.
rough, dark grey and box-type on lower stems, smooth above, grey-brown and coppery to bronze-grey and pink-grey, or smooth throughout.
smooth throughout, grey and creamy whiteover yellow, tan or pale salmon, shedding in conspicuous long ribbons.
rough, fibrous, grey-brown, on lower trunks and large branches; smooth bark light grey or pale coppery brown or cream, often decorticating in ribbons or strips.
on trunk partly rough to fully rough, often extending to larger branches, grey, box type; smooth bark grey to green, occasionally pink to brown.

smooth throughout, often with scattered tardily deciduous flakes, white to mottled white and pale grey-brown over cream or pale yellow; bark of saplings fibrous on stems, becoming smooth as size increases.
minnirichi on trunk and branches, red to red-brown.
smooth throughout, pinkish brown to green, shedding in ribbons.
rough throughout, coarsely stringy, grey to grey-brown and deeply furrowed.
rough and extending often tosmallest branches, fibrous, peppermint-type, dark grey, or branches ca 5 cm diameter smooth, cream, pale grey or yellow-grey.
smooth, white over salmon to pink, shedding in long ribbons.
rough to 10-15 cm diameter branches, box-type or finely tessellated, grey or mottled grey and white; smooth bark pale grey to coppery.
smooth throughout, light grey to white-grey over tan or pinkish,and cream, shedding seasonally in long ribbons.
usually rough over most of the lower stem, sometimes extending to the larger branches, fibrous, light grey to brown; upper stem mostly smooth-barked, smooth bark grey to brown to cream.
smooth throughout, grey-brown and light grey over pinkish, grey ribbons may shed tardily at the base of stems.
rough, grey to grey-brown to white, box-type or flaky, on part or all of stems, often extending to branches ca 5 cm diameter; smooth above, pale grey to pink-salmon or pale brown.
rough over whole trunk and to 10 cm diameter branches, box-type, at times tessellated in part, grey; smooth bark of branches white to cream and green-brown.
rough over part or all of trunk, grey-brown to dark-grey, flaky, or smooth throughout and brown-grey to coppery, olive green or pinkish grey, branches smooth.
rough to small branches, coarsely stringy and deeply, longitudinally furrowed, grey to grey-brown.
rough over part or all of trunk, grey, fibrous or shedding imperfectly in broad strips, smooth above, or on smaller stems smooth throughout, whitish grey over yellowish or salmon pink.
rough over part or all of trunks, fibrous, firm, grey to grey-black, smooth grey over light creamy grey above.
